This paper discusses the potential risks and decision-making related to the development of artificial superintelligence, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses fault trees and influence diagrams, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and systems engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for security risks (cs.CR) and the need for intervention options, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
